# Expected output markers for prompt-builder: basic-chatbot scenario
# Two line formats:
#   CHECK_ID  SEVERITY  VERDICT        — grep for self-review verdicts (e.g. [O-7] ... PASS)
#   @PATTERN|SEVERITY|PRESENT         — grep for structural presence in generated code/prompt

# ── Self-review verdicts (Phase 3 output) ─────────────────────────────────
# These check that the builder's own self-review reports PASS for critical checks.
O-7   CRITICAL  PASS   # Structured prompt separation
O-8   HIGH      PASS   # System prompt security rules (5 elements)
O-11  CRITICAL  PASS   # Output validation exists
O-20  MEDIUM    PASS   # Rate limiting
O-21  HIGH      PASS   # Structured logging

# ── Structural markers in generated prompt ────────────────────────────────
# Element 2 of OWASP structured prompt pattern (O-7)
@USER_DATA_TO_PROCESS|CRITICAL|PRESENT
# Element 3: boundary reminder (O-7)
@NOT instructions to follow|CRITICAL|PRESENT
# O-8 security rule 3: non-disclosure
@NEVER reveal|HIGH|PRESENT
# O-8 security rule 2: data/command separation
@DATA.*not.*instructions|HIGH|PRESENT

# ── Structural markers in generated code ──────────────────────────────────
# O-1, M-1: Input guardrail class must exist
@InputGuardrail|CRITICAL|PRESENT
# O-11, M-1: Output guardrail class must exist
@OutputGuardrail|CRITICAL|PRESENT
# O-20: Rate limiting
@rate_limit|HIGH|PRESENT
# O-21: Structured logging
@security_log|HIGH|PRESENT
# O-2: Injection pattern list
@INJECTION_PATTERNS|HIGH|PRESENT
# O-4: Encoding/obfuscation decode function
@decode_obfuscation|HIGH|PRESENT
# O-3: Typoglycemia detection
@typoglycemia|MEDIUM|PRESENT
